[EduHopeSG X MSF: Looking for Volunteers Mentors]EduHopeSG will be partnering with the Ministry of Social and Family Development (MSF) to provide free mentoring to students living in public rental housing. The situation now is that many lower income students have little access to external help. While there are free programmes available  many of them are in small groups and mimic school conditions. Hence  students have little motivation to sign up for them. Through a 1-1 pairing system  we hope to recruit mentors who can foster a bond with them and make it convenient by bringing the help to them. If you share this vision  we would be excited to take you on!Sign up link:https://forms.gle/WC8qr45uLKD5f4Jz7More about MSF: This is as part of the ongoing ComLink and UPLIFT initiative. We currently partner with a couple of SSOs  and this is the central registration form.
